1
00:00:00,560 --> 00:00:02,520
Kee, as your mom, I'm
asking you to listen to me.

2
00:00:03,960 --> 00:00:04,960
"Mom"?

3
00:00:07,280 --> 00:00:09,480
How dare you call yourself my mom?

4
00:00:12,040 --> 00:00:14,400
You tricked me into believing you had died,

5
00:00:16,280 --> 00:00:18,920
and you still have the nerve
to call yourself my mom?!

6
00:00:23,960 --> 00:00:25,920
I know you're very angry with me,

7
00:00:26,960 --> 00:00:28,840
but I want you to listen
to what I have to say.

8
00:00:29,440 --> 00:00:30,680
I have my own reasons.

9
00:00:30,760 --> 00:00:32,760
That's not true!

10
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:41,240
You left me to struggle all by myself.

11
00:00:42,440 --> 00:00:44,160
I've lived in confusion!

12
00:00:44,680 --> 00:00:47,440
I've lived for revenge. How
could you do this to me?!

13
00:00:51,160 --> 00:00:52,280
How could you?!

14
00:00:52,320 --> 00:00:53,880
I thought it was for the best,

15
00:00:54,240 --> 00:00:55,240
for everyone's sake!

16
00:00:56,080 --> 00:00:57,560
I wanted to protect you!

17
00:00:58,080 --> 00:00:59,320
Protect me?

18
00:01:02,440 --> 00:01:05,360
Out of all the ways you
could have protected me,

19
00:01:07,520 --> 00:01:10,480
you chose to disappear
and call it protection?!

20
00:01:13,600 --> 00:01:14,680
You know what?

21
00:01:16,160 --> 00:01:18,080
Seeing you standing right here

22
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:22,840
is even more painful than
thinking you were dead!!

23
00:01:27,520 --> 00:01:28,520
I'm sorry.

24
00:01:34,480 --> 00:01:36,440
But I want you to know

25
00:01:38,960 --> 00:01:40,840
that Weiling isn't who you thought she was.

26
00:01:48,360 --> 00:01:50,200
What lies are you going to tell me now?

27
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:52,200
What lies?!

28
00:01:55,240 --> 00:01:56,960
You want to lie to me so much, huh?

29
00:01:58,360 --> 00:01:59,360
Go on.

30
00:01:59,720 --> 00:02:01,520
You've been lying to
me all this time anyway.

31
00:02:02,040 --> 00:02:03,040
Say it!

32
00:02:03,560 --> 00:02:04,560
Say it now!

33
00:02:08,160 --> 00:02:10,000
I'm here to tell you the truth.

34
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:15,000
I want you to know that Weiling
wasn't the one who hurt our family.

35
00:02:16,280 --> 00:02:17,880
She was the one who helped us.

36
00:02:18,760 --> 00:02:20,760
If you just give me a chance to explain,

37
00:02:22,120 --> 00:02:23,120
you'll realize

38
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:25,960
and understand who was behind everything.

39
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:31,560
Your chance was there 20 years ago.

40
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:38,200
You missed it.

41
00:04:11,320 --> 00:04:13,160
Are you okay?

42
00:04:21,480 --> 00:04:22,920
Are you satisfied now,

43
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:25,120
seeing me like this?

44
00:04:26,520 --> 00:04:27,920
Are you satisfied now?!

45
00:04:30,280 --> 00:04:32,320
It's not about satisfaction.

46
00:04:33,760 --> 00:04:35,520
Even though I'm still angry at you,

47
00:04:36,360 --> 00:04:39,360
I understand you better
after listening to your story.

48
00:04:43,280 --> 00:04:44,560
Want to curse at me?

49
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:48,000
Go ahead, curse at me.

50
00:04:48,280 --> 00:04:50,656
Curse me out as much as I
deserve for what I've done to you!

51
00:04:50,680 --> 00:04:52,000
I'm despicable!

52
00:04:52,200 --> 00:04:53,280
I destroyed your life!

53
00:04:53,480 --> 00:04:55,600
Curse at me, Lalin. Why
are you just standing there?!

54
00:04:55,640 --> 00:04:58,280
Say it! Just say anything! Say it!

55
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:02,200
I'm not gonna say anything,

56
00:05:05,920 --> 00:05:07,320
but I'll be right here

57
00:05:07,520 --> 00:05:08,520
next to you.

58
00:05:09,280 --> 00:05:10,400
I won't go anywhere.

59
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:14,320
Just tell me when you're ready.

60
00:05:15,840 --> 00:05:17,360
I can wait. It'll be fine.

61
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:19,240
I can wait.

62
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:29,560
It's over, Lalin.

63
00:05:31,120 --> 00:05:32,520
It's over for us.

64
00:05:33,360 --> 00:05:34,920
It's over.

65
00:05:43,960 --> 00:05:46,280
Stop being so good to me.

66
00:05:47,120 --> 00:05:48,440
Stop it.

67
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:51,960
You need to be where you belong.

68
00:05:52,160 --> 00:05:54,040
I don't deserve you!

69
00:05:55,160 --> 00:05:57,760
This is bad enough as it is.

70
00:05:58,920 --> 00:05:59,920
No.

71
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:03,080
I won't accept this.

72
00:06:04,600 --> 00:06:07,640
You know too well I'm not
the type to give up easily.

73
00:06:11,280 --> 00:06:13,520
We're both hurt,

74
00:06:14,080 --> 00:06:16,080
but we're supposed to
get through this together!

75
00:06:24,880 --> 00:06:26,440
Give yourself a chance.

76
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:33,560
I'll wait for you to come back.

77
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:22,040
Auntie, please wait right here.

78
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:23,920
I'll go get my mom for you.

79
00:08:57,520 --> 00:08:59,200
Excuse me, then.

80
00:09:15,960 --> 00:09:17,280
You haven't changed one bit.

81
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:24,400
Of course, I have.

82
00:09:26,880 --> 00:09:27,880
A lot, actually.

83
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:43,040
I still remember so vividly

84
00:09:44,120 --> 00:09:45,480
the last day we met.

85
00:09:58,080 --> 00:09:59,080
I know

86
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:02,920
it would mean nothing if I apologized now.

87
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:08,240
No one would forgive me.

88
00:10:09,760 --> 00:10:10,960
Aren't you going to try?

89
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:15,320
I've been waiting for an
explanation for 20 years.

90
00:10:20,240 --> 00:10:21,600
I saw that you were happy.

91
00:10:23,960 --> 00:10:25,320
I saw that you had a family,

92
00:10:26,800 --> 00:10:27,800
a child,

93
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:33,520
and a good reputation in society.

94
00:10:36,280 --> 00:10:39,320
You have everything I could never give you.

95
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:42,320
If I came back...

96
00:10:45,320 --> 00:10:46,440
If you chose me,

97
00:10:48,520 --> 00:10:49,680
everything would fall apart.

98
00:10:50,120 --> 00:10:53,040
- So you decided for me…
- Couldn't you just let me fall apart on my own?

99
00:10:54,200 --> 00:10:55,560
Why would you decide for me?!

100
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:59,880
What about our promise
to fight it all together?!

101
00:11:01,280 --> 00:11:02,960
Just the two of us.

102
00:11:05,880 --> 00:11:07,600
Why did you just decide it all on your own?

103
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:10,720
For 20 years, you left
someone who loved you waiting.

104
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:13,000
I never even knew if
you were dead or alive.

105
00:11:13,480 --> 00:11:15,040
Isn't that too much?!

106
00:11:24,520 --> 00:11:25,880
I have no excuse

107
00:11:30,360 --> 00:11:31,480
except for an apology.

108
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:48,280
I used to think that my happiness

109
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:53,680
was seeing you and Kee happy,

110
00:11:54,760 --> 00:11:55,760
and that if I...

111
00:11:57,920 --> 00:11:59,960
If I watched you two
from far away, I'd be okay.

112
00:12:00,440 --> 00:12:02,960
But I never thought that
everything would turn out this way...

113
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:04,960
That's because you assumed everything.

114
00:12:11,160 --> 00:12:12,960
We've known each other for so long.

115
00:12:14,240 --> 00:12:16,840
Have I ever once left you behind?

116
00:12:42,240 --> 00:12:43,640
I miss you so much.

117
00:12:46,920 --> 00:12:50,520
♫ Never a second could I forget you ♫

118
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:54,480
♫ You're still here when
night comes through ♫

119
00:12:54,840 --> 00:12:59,080
♫ I don't wish to wake up sometimes, ♫

120
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:02,400
♫ Afraid that you'd say goodbye ♫

121
00:13:03,520 --> 00:13:06,336
Just seeing you again is
beyond my wildest dreams.

122
00:13:06,360 --> 00:13:13,360
♫ To say that I'll never stop missing you ♫

123
00:13:14,880 --> 00:13:16,160
Don't ever leave me again.

124
00:13:17,400 --> 00:13:19,120
That way, we won't have to miss each other.

125
00:13:47,720 --> 00:13:53,920
♫ Do you know I miss you? ♫

126
00:14:05,369 --> 00:14:06,689
How are you doing, Uncle Kengkad?

127
00:14:07,169 --> 00:14:08,649
Are you better now?

128
00:14:10,129 --> 00:14:12,169
I'm sorry I didn't visit you.

129
00:14:15,249 --> 00:14:16,489
Any updates on the matter?

130
00:14:17,449 --> 00:14:20,489
I can assure you that it
wasn't one of Weiling's people.

131
00:14:21,609 --> 00:14:24,369
Actually, I've been keeping an
eye on this situation for a while.

132
00:14:25,409 --> 00:14:28,209
I looked into it, and I
think I know who it was.

133
00:14:28,369 --> 00:14:29,769
I was going to tell you, Ms. King,

134
00:14:30,529 --> 00:14:32,129
but he got to me first.

135
00:14:34,649 --> 00:14:35,649
Who was he?

136
00:14:45,729 --> 00:14:47,409
This is the man who works for Arisa.

137
00:14:47,889 --> 00:14:48,649
That's right.

138
00:14:48,889 --> 00:14:52,169
From what I've learned about
what happened to your father, Chet,

139
00:14:52,769 --> 00:14:54,649
it might've been this man's doing too.

140
00:15:12,569 --> 00:15:13,569
Hey.

141
00:15:13,889 --> 00:15:14,889
Hey...

142
00:15:16,209 --> 00:15:17,489
- Ugh...
- Ugh...

143
00:15:19,929 --> 00:15:21,489
Why did you sigh like that?

144
00:15:22,449 --> 00:15:23,769
Going through a rough time?

145
00:15:25,129 --> 00:15:26,289
It's pretty rough.

146
00:15:28,169 --> 00:15:29,969
And why did you sigh like that?

147
00:15:32,289 --> 00:15:33,289
I've

148
00:15:33,369 --> 00:15:34,889
been through a difficult situation.

149
00:15:43,929 --> 00:15:44,929
Hey,

150
00:15:45,569 --> 00:15:47,089
wanna grab a bite together?

151
00:15:47,729 --> 00:15:48,729
To cheer us up.

152
00:16:02,249 --> 00:16:04,289
Got anything you want
to get off your chest?

153
00:16:05,169 --> 00:16:06,209
Let's share.

154
00:16:09,129 --> 00:16:10,689
It's nothing.

155
00:16:11,569 --> 00:16:14,649
It's just that I found out
who caused my dad's death.

156
00:16:17,609 --> 00:16:19,809
I'll see this through to the end.

157
00:16:22,889 --> 00:16:24,049
Part of me is relieved,

158
00:16:25,529 --> 00:16:27,249
but I also feel uneasy for the victim.

159
00:16:29,489 --> 00:16:31,449
Anything I can help you with?

160
00:16:33,049 --> 00:16:34,289
It's fine.

161
00:16:34,529 --> 00:16:35,769
I'll handle it.

162
00:16:40,049 --> 00:16:41,049
Thanks.

163
00:16:42,809 --> 00:16:43,809
What about you?

164
00:16:45,809 --> 00:16:46,889
I

165
00:16:47,049 --> 00:16:48,609
Just feel bad for my boss.

166
00:16:50,609 --> 00:16:52,449
With everything she's been through,

167
00:16:55,529 --> 00:16:57,369
she must have been so confused.

168
00:16:58,489 --> 00:16:59,689
Out of nowhere,

169
00:16:59,929 --> 00:17:02,449
her mom, who she thought
was dead, just showed up.

170
00:17:03,649 --> 00:17:05,689
Not to mention the
situation with Ms. Weiling,

171
00:17:06,249 --> 00:17:08,809
which seems to have turned into
an even bigger misunderstanding.

172
00:17:10,049 --> 00:17:11,089
Worst of all

173
00:17:11,849 --> 00:17:13,889
is probably what's going on with Ms. Lalin.

174
00:17:15,209 --> 00:17:16,209
Gosh.

175
00:17:17,009 --> 00:17:18,289
I don't think

176
00:17:19,009 --> 00:17:21,289
my boss can handle all of this.

177
00:17:22,369 --> 00:17:24,249
She's really fragile on
the inside, you know.

178
00:17:25,929 --> 00:17:28,249
I think this kind of thing takes time.

179
00:17:32,489 --> 00:17:33,929
I agree.

180
00:17:35,329 --> 00:17:36,449
But

181
00:17:36,609 --> 00:17:38,289
if time doesn't help,

182
00:17:38,449 --> 00:17:39,769
I'll tell you right now

183
00:17:40,329 --> 00:17:43,889
I'll be the one helping her.

184
00:17:46,369 --> 00:17:49,329
You seem to enjoy sticking your
nose in other people's business.

185
00:17:50,889 --> 00:17:52,649
But you've gotta help me, too.

186
00:17:53,329 --> 00:17:54,809
We're a team.

187
00:17:56,649 --> 00:17:57,649
Cheers.

188
00:18:08,369 --> 00:18:09,449
By the way

189
00:18:10,529 --> 00:18:12,569
how did you find my boss's mom?

190
00:18:13,209 --> 00:18:14,209
Tell me everything.

191
00:18:15,129 --> 00:18:16,209
Uh...

192
00:18:16,649 --> 00:18:19,449
So, Ms. Lalin came to see me at home,

193
00:18:19,649 --> 00:18:22,249
and she asked me to look into Ms. Arisa.

194
00:18:56,369 --> 00:18:58,209
I want this bracelet

195
00:18:58,889 --> 00:19:00,169
to be a reminder

196
00:19:01,649 --> 00:19:03,889
of the days we have each other.

197
00:19:26,089 --> 00:19:27,929
But ever since we crossed paths,

198
00:19:29,449 --> 00:19:31,689
there was never a
glimpse of darkness again.

199
00:19:32,209 --> 00:19:33,889
I promise

200
00:19:33,929 --> 00:19:36,169
I will treasure this light

201
00:19:37,289 --> 00:19:39,169
for as long as I shall live.

202
00:20:35,369 --> 00:20:36,369
Boss!

203
00:20:37,209 --> 00:20:38,489
Boss, it's fine.

204
00:20:42,769 --> 00:20:44,609
I'll have the maid take care of it.

205
00:20:48,729 --> 00:20:50,249
It's been days,

206
00:20:51,009 --> 00:20:52,449
and you still don't feel better?

207
00:20:58,409 --> 00:20:59,409
Boss,

208
00:20:59,689 --> 00:21:01,449
we're gonna have a meeting off-site.

209
00:21:02,249 --> 00:21:04,369
What meeting? I didn't know about it.

210
00:21:05,209 --> 00:21:07,169
Since the case became messy earlier,

211
00:21:07,569 --> 00:21:09,569
you'll have to sort it out
with your partners now.

212
00:21:11,169 --> 00:21:12,529
Have someone handle it.

213
00:21:13,609 --> 00:21:14,609
That won't do.

214
00:21:16,249 --> 00:21:17,249
It's just

215
00:21:17,449 --> 00:21:18,929
I've already scheduled it, Boss.

216
00:21:20,129 --> 00:21:21,129
Please go

217
00:21:21,769 --> 00:21:23,649
before things get worse.

218
00:21:54,209 --> 00:21:55,209
Oh, hey.

219
00:21:55,929 --> 00:21:56,929
What are you doing here?

220
00:21:58,289 --> 00:22:00,809
At first, I was gonna come
here to talk to you about the intel,

221
00:22:01,289 --> 00:22:02,969
but seeing the state you're in,

222
00:22:03,689 --> 00:22:04,929
I don't think it's a good time.

223
00:22:05,169 --> 00:22:06,449
I'm sorry.

224
00:22:06,849 --> 00:22:08,649
I'm not in the mood for guests today.

225
00:22:09,689 --> 00:22:12,089
What do you mean by
that? I'm here as a friend.

226
00:22:14,649 --> 00:22:17,009
It can feel pretty cramped
just staying indoors.

227
00:22:18,089 --> 00:22:19,649
How about we go outside?

228
00:22:22,049 --> 00:22:23,289
I don't have the energy to.

229
00:22:24,049 --> 00:22:25,609
Being in the same place

230
00:22:25,849 --> 00:22:27,329
will bring all the memories

231
00:22:27,729 --> 00:22:28,809
flooding back.

232
00:22:29,969 --> 00:22:32,169
Trust me, let's go do something outside.

233
00:22:41,689 --> 00:22:44,729
Wanna see the menu?
The food here is really good.

234
00:22:50,089 --> 00:22:52,049
I'm gonna use the restroom.

235
00:22:53,649 --> 00:22:55,929
Want me to order anything for you

236
00:22:56,289 --> 00:22:57,449
so the food comes on time?

237
00:22:57,769 --> 00:22:59,129
Anything. You decide.

238
00:23:07,249 --> 00:23:08,889
Uh, Boss.

239
00:23:09,289 --> 00:23:10,449
Please go in first.

240
00:23:10,649 --> 00:23:11,969
I forgot some documents.

241
00:23:15,449 --> 00:23:16,449
You're holding them.

242
00:23:17,009 --> 00:23:18,889
Uh, they're in another envelope.

243
00:23:19,449 --> 00:23:20,689
Go on in.

244
00:23:21,409 --> 00:23:23,249
I'll be right with you.

245
00:23:38,569 --> 00:23:40,049
Hey, wait!

246
00:23:49,049 --> 00:23:50,849
How long are you gonna
keep pushing me away?

247
00:23:53,249 --> 00:23:54,569
Stop avoiding me.

248
00:23:56,929 --> 00:23:58,169
I'm not pushing you away

249
00:23:59,489 --> 00:24:00,489
or avoiding you.

250
00:24:03,129 --> 00:24:04,449
I'm just not ready.

251
00:24:07,849 --> 00:24:08,849
Hey,

252
00:24:09,609 --> 00:24:13,089
maybe it's time we face the truth,

253
00:24:14,089 --> 00:24:15,969
even though it's painful.

254
00:24:17,129 --> 00:24:21,009
Maybe it could be the start of healing.

255
00:24:23,449 --> 00:24:24,769
And I'm

256
00:24:25,129 --> 00:24:28,209
tired of acting like I don't care about you.

257
00:24:36,129 --> 00:24:37,889
Don't you see me in a bad light?

258
00:24:38,689 --> 00:24:40,889
Don't you feel even a little
anger or hatred toward me?

259
00:24:42,729 --> 00:24:44,849
After I found out the truth,

260
00:24:46,529 --> 00:24:48,169
you can say I'm stupid

261
00:24:49,689 --> 00:24:52,009
or too generous,

262
00:24:56,409 --> 00:24:58,049
but I can't bring myself to hate you.

263
00:25:14,169 --> 00:25:15,849
Please go see your mom.

264
00:25:16,969 --> 00:25:19,529
She probably wants to
explain everything to you.

265
00:25:43,809 --> 00:25:45,449
I'm ready for the truth.

266
00:26:06,449 --> 00:26:08,569
Weiling and I have been
friends since university.

267
00:26:14,569 --> 00:26:15,809
She was my best friend

268
00:26:20,249 --> 00:26:22,009
and closet person

269
00:26:27,449 --> 00:26:29,609
until I had to marry your dad

270
00:26:32,129 --> 00:26:34,129
for the sake of our family's business.

271
00:26:35,449 --> 00:26:37,129
It seemed like a happy ending,

272
00:26:38,209 --> 00:26:39,969
but no one knew

273
00:26:41,409 --> 00:26:43,529
it was the start of a nightmare.

274
00:27:03,209 --> 00:27:04,929
Still using that pen?

275
